# Planning target resolution

Planning protocol branches act on a specific `.plan.md` under the **`.sedea/operations/`** union. The target is resolved from **session input, chat context, and structured choices** ‚Äî not from the IDE focused-file list alone (IDE state can drift from planning intent).

## Sedea input channel (planning picks)

When a turn **requires a user reply** before you continue (pick a planning branch, confirm a target plan, choose list index **N** for **`new-plan`**), collect that pick through **AskQuestion** or **`MC_ASKQUESTION_V1`** per [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/2_ask-question-instructions.mdc`](../../sedea/rules/2_ask-question-instructions.mdc). **Supersedes** the former *AskQuestion or numbered bullet list* option in this rule. Mission Control **AskQuestion** also exposes **free-form text** on the modal ‚Äî use it for extra instruction alongside an `option` pick; do not reopen choices in prose chat.

**Snapshot table (information-only).** The *Next viable moves* column may use **numbered rows** so the developer can read the plan tree in one glance. Those numbers are **reference labels** for the snapshot only ‚Äî when a pick is required, the choosable paths live in **AskQuestion** `options`, not as a prose menu in the agent message.

**Transcript boundary.** When the snapshot is long, use two assistant turns per [`.sedea/centers/sedea/rules/2_ask-question-instructions.mdc`](../../sedea/rules/2_ask-question-instructions.mdc) ¬ß *Mission Control transcript boundary*: (1) snapshot only; (2) **AskQuestion** only with one `option` per move (brief `label`; full branch + target in `prompt` if needed).

