## Planning readiness vs ship (do not conflate)

Three different signals appear in plan-and-deliver; advancing one does **not** advance the others.

| Signal | Set by | Means | Does **not** mean |
|--------|--------|-------|-------------------|
| **`readyForImplementation`** | **`pr-plan`** child `outputs` | Planning ¬ß¬ß 1‚Äì4 are drafted; developer may open **`coding-session`** | Worktree may open; ¬ß¬ß 5‚Äì8 complete; Squad Leader ¬ß8 `phase` past `not-started` |
| **`plan-ws-completeness.mjs` exit 0** | Script on PR plan path | PR plan ¬ß¬ß 5‚Äì8 lack blocking `_TBD_` for worktree handoff | **`coding-session`** already running; PR open |
| **`developerApprovedImplementation`** | **`coding-session`** after worktree-open gate | Layer-2 consent to implement on a worktree | Dispatch ship ledger auto-updated (leader ¬ß8 still needs recap) |

**`pr-plan` does not spawn `coding-session`.** After **`pr-plan`**, the developer starts **`coding-session`** on a **detached** lane (phrase, snapshot, or new session). Do not implement on the **`pr-plan`** lane because `readyForImplementation` is true.

